{
  "text": "PM-toxin produced by M. zeae-maydis is structurally related to T-toxin and involves a gene cluster that contains homologs of TOX1 genes (PKS1, RED1 and RED2; [CITATION_1] . Although the three genes are required for PM-toxin biosynthesis in M. zeae-maydis, this gene cluster does not provide any additional information on the biosynthesis of T-toxin.",
